---
import PageLayout from '../../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import { url } from '../../lib/paths';
---

<PageLayout
  title="For learners"
  description="What to expect from Free Ham Radio Curriculum workshops in your community."
  current="start"
>
  <Breadcrumbs
    items={[
      { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
      { label: 'For learners' },
    ]}
  />
  <h1>For learners</h1>
  <p>
    Free Ham Radio Curriculum materials are used in <strong>local classes and club events</strong> — not as a
    self-paced online course. If you found this site, a trainer in your community may be planning
    a workshop, or you are curious what is available.
  </p>

  <h2>What you might learn</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><a href={url('/curriculum/phone/emergency-radio-101/')}>Emergency Radio 101</a> — why radio matters when everything else fails</li>
    <li><a href={url('/curriculum/phone/ham-101/')}>Ham 101</a> — introduction to amateur radio and licensing</li>
    <li><a href={url('/curriculum/activities/fox-hunt/')}>Fox Hunt</a> — find a hidden transmitter, learn about antennas</li>
    <li><a href={url('/curriculum/phone/ham-hf-practical-skills/')}>Ham HF Practical Skills</a> — get on HF and make a contact</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>License milestones</h2>
  <p>
    Many workshops require no license at all. Others expect a Technician or General ticket — the unit
    page always states what is required.
  </p>

  <h2>Find a class</h2>
  <p>
    This site publishes materials for trainers. To attend a workshop, check with your local radio
    club, library, or mutual aid group — or ask an Elmer you know if they plan to lead one.
  </p>

  <p style="margin-top: 2rem;">
    <a class="btn btn-primary" href={url('/curriculum/')}>Browse curriculum</a>
  </p>
</PageLayout>
